    "details": {
      "blurb": "Drunken watch sergeant; future ally",
      "languages": {
        "details": "",
        "value": [
          "common"
        ]
      },
      "level": {
        "value": 4
      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> a recurring NPC — a well-liked Korvosan Guard watch sergeant (Vencarlo Orisini's expelled student) drowning his despair in drink. This 'fight' is meant to be survived and <strong>defused</strong>, not a kill.</p><p><strong>Defusing him:</strong> commiserate (@Check[type:diplomacy|dc:20], or a Deception vs. his Perception) and he sobers up; @Check[type:society|dc:18] recognizes the sergeant he was. A lesser restoration sobers him instantly. Escorted to Citadel Volshyenek, his fellow guards clean him up and he becomes a grateful ally.</p><p><strong>If he duels:</strong> he limits attacks to the PC who accepted the duel; if another PC strikes him he cries 'Foul!' and flails at random foes. <strong>Morale:</strong> surrenders rather than dies. Award XP as if defeated whether he is beaten or talked down.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
        "authors": "",
        "license": "OGL",
        "remaster": true
      }
